17: Kugui locks herself in her room, despite Ryouki and co.'s attempts to coax her out. Suizen offers a suggestion—travel to Kugui's home village, in order to ascertain the dragon's true nature and learn more about Kugui. Taking the suggestion, Ryouki bursts into Kugui's room and drags her out on a date, before leading her and the rest of the group to the village.
21: At the ravaged village, Ryouki explains to Kugui that she aspires to paint like her, and that her art has the potential to make dreams come true. She cheekily prods at Kugui's pride, claiming that she'll one day overtake the disheartened girl if she quits painting now. The two have a heart-to-heart, and Kugui resolves to paint again.
25: Kugui realizes the dragon is a manifestation of her fears, and in order to fully control her power, she must conquer the dragon first. With her pride and her life on the line, she summons the dragon once more for a final showdown.
27: Kugui dreams of her past, finally remembering how she first learned of the dragon. When she wakes, it is time for the competition. She and Ryouki finish painting their yokai, but Gramp Zigza insists that Kugui brings them to life for a grand finale—one that involves an epic battle.
29: Suizen and Mizuchi reflect over the past week and Kugui's growth. In the meantime, Alk and co. visit Gramp Zigza, hoping to see Kugui, but she is out with Ryouki in the mountains. The two girls have another heart-to-heart, treasuring the bond they have with one another, as they enjoy another day of art and adventure.
1: Suizen hears that Inaho and Gramp Zigza are planning to make another volume of the Yokai Encyclopedia. Fearing the dangers another book would pose, he calls upon Kugui, an artist as well as his subordinate, and Alk and friends to oversee its creation.
2: Suizen wishes for Kugui to be the editor of the Yokai Encyclopedia's second volume. As for Alk and co., they are meant to watch over Kugui, as her power brought a painting to life and destroyed her village when she was younger—though she doesn't have clear memories of the incident. The group travels to visit Inaho, who demands a battle before she assists them.
4: Inaho brings the group to Gramp Zigza, who is less than pleased to hear that Kugui wants to interfere with the encyclopedia's creation. Just as he is about to kick them out, his disciple Ryouki interrupts and gives Kugui a chance to show off her art. Now intrigued, Gramp Zigza proposes a competition between Ryouki and Kugui—if Kugui wins, she'll be allowed to be the encyclopedia's editor. Ryouki and Kugui accept, and they are given a week to improve their yokai art.
8: Kugui learns that Ryouki has only been painting for 3 months and is briefly crestfallen by how much more talented Ryouki is. However, her resolve not to lose is strengthened. She finishes a yokai painting and, under the encouragement of Light and co., brings it to life, but is ultimately unable to control it. The group prepares to take the creation down.
12: Ryouki tries to cheer up Kugui, who is depressed at how she could not control her creation, with a new idea—paint a fake yokai and see if this one will behave. Ryouki brings Kugui a painting of a dragon she made up, but Kugui somehow recognizes it. Feeling her memories come back, Kugui paints the dragon and brings it to life. Unfortunately, the creation immediately attacks.
14: With Suizen and Mizuchi's help, Alk and co. are able to put down the dragon. Suizen explains that the dragon is actually a shikigami that has bound itself to Kugui, and that it might be the same creature that destroyed her village when she was younger. Disheartened and fearful of hurting more people, Kugui states that she will never paint again and secludes herself in her room. Ryouki, however, refuses to let things stand and decides to find a way to help Kugui.

1: Mary visits Wilfred in his lab with the intention of confessing her feelings to him. She gives him a thoughtful gift but leaves without accomplishing her goal.
2: Mary is teaching Stella how to prepare chocolates when she hears Wilfred outside. In a hurry, he falls and injures himself, but Mary heals him. Once he leaves, Mary tells Stella and the others how she feels about him, and Operation: Snag the Childhood Friend is launched.
3: Deeply in love, Mary tells the others that she wants to have a beach date with Wilfred using Nate's VR equipment.
4: Even with the perfect conditions afforded by the carefully planned VR beach date, Mary fails to confess her feelings. When told that the operation will be called off, Mary explains why she ran away from the opportunity and reassures the others of her intention to confess. With that, the meeting for Operation: Snag the Childhood Friend 2 begins.
5: After being grilled by Nate and the others, Mary becomes emboldened and asks Wilfred for another date.
6: Mary and Wilfred enjoy an all-day date with each other. Standing on a bridge they share a nostalgic memory of, the two attempt to confess their feelings to each other. However, strange black sheep golems suddenly appear and start revealing the deep, hidden feelings of the people in the city.
7: Rejecting the words of the black sheep, Mary and Wilfred express their feelings to one another in their own words. As the flock of black sheep continue to be attacked by Reticia and Nate, they merge into one massive sheep golem.
9: With the golem defeated, Wilfred and Mary go on a date at night as a newly formed couple. There, Wilfred holds Mary's hand for the first time.

1: Alk and co. visit Paradise Isle for yet another summer vacation, this time opting to check out a nice and quiet spot called Miner's Front. Once there, they split up, with Primula's group wandering over to the lighthouse. There, they run across a somber-looking girl holding a camera.
2: The somber girl's name is Echo, and she happens to be the daughter of the man in charge of the float's redevelopment project. Primula and co. talk to Echo and find out that there's a spot on the island very dear to her memories. This special place is in a restricted area, but the gang decide to head there regardless. Meanwhile, Bulleta gets some intel about what's really happening with the redevelopment project.
3: After splitting off from Alk and co., Primula and her party decided to explore past the off-access area and take a look at the island's limestone cave. Echo talks about her memories and the gang all take a lovely photo together. Just then, however, Echo's father appears.
4: Echo gives her camera to Primula and argues with her father, before obediently leaving alongside him. Wishing to know more about how Echo feels, Primula and co. sneak into her estate to talk with her. Echo, unable to come to terms with her own weakness, rejects the kind words of Primula and the others.
5: Having been hurt before by her experiences with a woman named Narcissa, Echo continues to push Primula and the others away. Primula is deeply saddened by Echo's actions and storms off, tears in her eyes.
6: Unable to control herself and overwhelmed by emotions, Primula is consoled by Alk and the others. Meanwhile, Echo—who was unable to find the courage to go along with Primula—has tea with Parfait. The monster chef encourages Echo to reunite with Primula.
7: When the trio meet up again, they lay all their feelings out on the table and finally make up. Afterward, Echo learns of her father's weapon smuggling operation and resolves to confront him alongside Primula and the others. Alk and co. engage in combat with an armed helicopter that's on its way to intercept their advance.
9: After exchanging some key words with her father, Echo finally gets the resolve to visit the precious spot from her memories. She realizes that the area has been built over, and decides to create new memories instead. Later, Primula, Pythica, and Echo have a fun day out on the town exploring Paradise Isle.

8: Just as the failed experiments corner Alk, Sohvi, and Shywe, Nimbus and the gang come to their rescue.
9: Sohvi, having regained her memories, guides the gang to Deophrastus. Just as the group comes face-to-face with the mad scientist, Deo proclaims he will surpass humanity before being enveloped in a bright light.
10: Despite acquiring the power of the Devourer of Stars, Deophrastus continues to draw out more power, causing the world to begin falling apart. Just then, Shywe receives a prophecy that, in order to reclaim her powers, she must sacrifice Alk.
11: By refusing the false prophecy of the Devourer of Stars, Shywe finally learns to prioritize her own will. A powerful sprite reacts to her newfound passion and appears before her. With this new ally, Shywe and Alk take on Deophrastus.
13: Upon returning to Paradise Isle, Shywe is confronted with the reality of her feelings for Alk. Confused by this new emotion, Shywe tries to flee, but her friends pull her back before she can get herself into trouble again.
1: After some prodding from Inaho, the gang heads to Paradise Isle for a vacation. Among them is Shywe, determined to make her prophesized marriage to Alk a reality.
2: When Shywe tries to show the wonders of the sprites to Alk, she suddenly loses her connection to the sprites and strands them on a mysterious island. Still recovering from the fall, she and Alk are soon surrounded by hungry animals.
3: As Shywe acclimates to life without the power of the sprites, Alk does his best to provide them with food and shelter. That night, Shywe senses a mysterious power.
4: Back on Paradise Isle, Nimbus and the rest of the gang split up to find their missing friends. Meanwhile, Alk and Shywe stumble upon an amnesiac Sohvi.
5: When an abnormally normal Sohvi guides Alk and Shywe to the building she awoke in, they are accosted by a ferocious creature crying out for his love.
7: Just as Nimbus and co. find Alk and Shywe's footprints, Light contacts them with information on the island and its relation to the Devourer of Stars. Meanwhile, Alk, Shywe, and Sohvi arrive at a mysterious research facility.

17: The woman in white is named Adala and she seems to be an old "research partner" of Captain Zegra, though she tells Luca she is irritated that the old captain took all their research with him when he disappeared. Marina and co. come rushing to Luca's rescue and launch an attack on the enemy ship.
20: The party takes over the pirate vessel they were pursuing, but fails to find Luca on board. Illumine senses a distortion in the light ahead, which she disperses, revealing a massive submarine. Marina and Alk resolve to enter it and continue their search for Luca.
23: Adala takes Luca to see his father, Captain Zegra—albeit a version of him that has transcended his humanity. The captain's real legacy was not gold or wealth, but rather the ability to become more than human—to evolve beyond our limits. Marina and Alk infiltrate the submarine, rescue Luca, and attempt to flee.
26: Just when things start to look grim, Belsidia and Marina come to Alk's rescue, turning things around. Belsidia runs off to chase after a fleeing Adala, when the party suddenly hear a roar—it's Captain Zegra, in his draconic, altered form. Luca and Marina, having had enough of the Captain's misguided ways, choose to finally confront him head on.
28: As alarms continue to ring in the submarine, Marina and co. are completely stumped on how to escape. Suddenly, Stella and Amelie show up to rescue them, escorting them out safely. Luca, now armed with the vast knowledge handed down to him by Captain Zegra, heads off to return home, Genome Quartz in hand. Alk sees him off before returning to his interrupted vacation.
1: Marina awakes from an unpleasant dream to learn that the treasure of the legendary Captain Zegra has been found—and is going to be put up as a prize in a major casino. Marina, in full summer attire, makes her way to Alk and invites him to go on an adventure.
2: The party is enjoying a well-deserved rest on Paradise Isle, a man-made tropical resort island. Alice, riding on the shoulders of her escort Gerard, suddenly hears her kitten cry out and rushes to its aid. She then finds an unconscious beastfolk boy, whom she tries to care for—only to be rudely interrupted by a horde of mysterious monsters.
5: Upon hearing the name Crimson Blades, Luca asks Marina if she worked for his father, the infamous captain Zegra. Realizing who the boy is, Marina decides to show him her Genome Quartz. The two of them decide to team up to take back the remnants of Zegra's treasure that are being held at the casino.
9: Luca inquires as to Marina and his father's relationship, only to find out that she considers them archenemies. When speaking with Alk, Luca announces that he plans on getting stronger and keeping up with Alk. The next day, Naska and Marina take on the famous Money Muncher slot machine, all while Belsidia and another group infiltrate the casino's storage room.
12: Illumine channels an illusion on the slot machine to distract onlookers, but finds that doing so is taxing on her stamina. Suddenly, Alk and co. appear with a dragon hot on their tail. Happy to have a way to vent their frustrations about losing money at the casino, the group take down the massive foe.
14: Upon assembling all three Genome Quartz crystals, a recorded message from Captain Zegra is transmitted to everyone, inviting Marina and Luca to come to him. Just then, the group receives a message indicating their secret base is under attack. Alk and co. rush back to the aid of Gerard, who is defending their base valiantly, only to have a mysterious woman in white arrive and kidnap Luca.

1: On the rooftops of Qualia City, a city that has been in business for 520 years, a mercenary named Bulleta and her partner Love spot a ray of light in the distance. Sensing a call to adventure, they make their way toward it.
2: Bulleta saves Alk and the others from an attacker known as the Conductor. Love advises them to become troubleshooters if they hope to make a living in Qualia City, a place governed entirety by corporate ethos.
6: While enjoying their meal of AdTaste-flavored SoyMate, Alk and the others learn of AltMeme and Noxel, the two corporations that dominate Qualia City. Using their newly found intel, the group discovers that their attacker was working for DayAndNight, a Noxel Group subsidiary.
10: Bulleta decides to help Alk and the others infiltrate DAN, in hopes of showing her best friend what the real sky looks like beyond the neon skyline.
14: As Alk and the others head deeper into the DAN facility, the Conductor appears before them and takes a new weapon formation, codename: Big Band.
16: The Conductor, having been defeated, allows the group to pass. As they approach the altar, they're blindsided by an attack from Love, who reveals herself to be Mother Love, the true president of DAN. Bulleta uses a smoke bomb to narrowly escape with the others.
20: The group find themselves in a tight situation surrounded by Noxel enforcers when a man in an armored vehicle comes to their rescue. He introduces himself as King Johnson, the CEO of PBC, an AltMeme subsidiary. With no other viable methods of escape available, the group accepts his help.
24: The group finds Bulleta sulking in a tavern alone, reflecting on her recent fallout with Love. After Alk and company help her reaffirm her feelings, Bulleta finds the motivation to patch things up with Love.
28: While the Noxel and AltMeme enforcers engage in battle, the Conductor confirms Love's orders once again before facing off against Bulleta and the others in a final showdown.
30: After taking down the Conductor once again, Bulleta makes her way to Mother Love. Leaving nothing off the table, the estranged partners have a final clash of ideals and weapons.
32: The final attack between Bulleta and Love breaks a hole in the dome above, revealing a portion of the real sky. Love eventually steps down from her position at DAN and joins Bulleta to finally explore the skies together.

1: Alk and friends travel to an unexplored forest for a job, where they discover a castle and its town in the distance. As they approach, they see a mysterious robed man and the prince Razelt under attack, and drop in to save them.
4: The robed man introduces himself as Simon, and reveals that the town and castle were made by the princess Prika through creation magic. He asks the group to check on Prika in the castle, which they agree to. As they travel through town, Razelt accidentally discovers how fragile the structures are, before more Poppets appear and attack.
7: Alk and friends arrive at the castle, where they are verbally assaulted by Prika who mistakes them for someone else. The princess quickly realizes her mistake and invites them inside, eager to host people for the first time ever. She explains that her retainer Grey is missing, and that her only contact with the outside world is through letters with Prince Frau of Mosnia.
10: After comparing information, Prika reveals she has no idea why her Poppets are out of control, nor who Simon is. Her confusion only grows when Razelt tells her Mosnia was destroyed over 300 years ago. Determined to get answers, Prika grabs her prince's letters and asks Alk and friends to bring her to Simon.
13: While Alk and Razelt try to get the town gate open, Prika nervously explains that she has never gone outside before, but Stella is quick to calm her down. Simon suddenly appears from behind them, revealing that Prika is a weapon, and Grey was supposed to be her warden, before he attacks the group.
15: With the group in a pinch, Prika blasts open the gate and leads the group in a retreat, stepping into the outside world for the first time. That night, she has a heart-to-heart with Stella, who helps her acknowledge that her good memories with the prince were real, even if the prince himself wasn't.
18: Prika and company find the ruins of Mosnia, and confirm that Razelt spoke true—Mosnia hasn't existed for hundreds of years. Though her prince was never real, Prika is content enough to know that he was her friend, and that now she has Alk and company to call friends too. Determined to learn the truth about Grey, Prika asks everyone to take her back to Simon.
21: Alk and friends discover a letter and a will inside Simon's cabin, which reveal that Grey has passed away, and Prika is no princess. Simon reappears, blaming Prika's bloodline for the destruction of Mosnia, and claims that he will end her to free them from the curse of her existence.
24: In the middle of Simon's assault, Prika runs out to talk with him and follows him for a private conversation. Tensions come to a head, and the two face off with Poppets. Simon is finally driven into a corner, and summons up a decade's worth of mana to create Cair Oblivion.
26: Prika defeats Simon with one huge blow that reduces most of the town to rubble. In the aftermath, Prika pours her heart out to Simon and asks him to bring them to Grey's grave. There, the two have an earnest conversation and make up, with Prika deciding that they will be siblings from now on. Free from her castle confines at last, Prika parts with everyone, ready to see the world.

20: The party takes over the pirate vessel they were pursuing, but fails to find Luca on board. Illumine senses a distortion in the light ahead, which she disperses, revealing a massive submarine. Marina and Alk resolve to enter it and continue their search for Luca.
23: Adala takes Luca to see his father, Captain Zegra—albeit a version of him that has transcended his humanity. The captain's real legacy was not gold or wealth, but rather the ability to become more than human—to evolve beyond our limits. Marina and Alk infiltrate the submarine, rescue Luca, and attempt to flee.
26: Just when things start to look grim, Belsidia and Marina come to Alk's rescue, turning things around. Belsidia runs off to chase after a fleeing Adala, when the party suddenly hear a roar—it's Captain Zegra, in his draconic, altered form. Luca and Marina, having had enough of the Captain's misguided ways, choose to finally confront him head on.
28: As alarms continue to ring in the submarine, Marina and co. are completely stumped on how to escape. Suddenly, Stella and Amelie show up to rescue them, escorting them out safely. Luca, now armed with the vast knowledge handed down to him by Captain Zegra, heads off to return home, Genome Quartz in hand. Alk sees him off before returning to his interrupted vacation.

1: Suizen hears that Inaho and Gramp Zigza are planning to make another volume of the Yokai Encyclopedia. Fearing the dangers another book would pose, he calls upon Kugui, an artist as well as his subordinate, and Alk and friends to oversee its creation.
2: Suizen wishes for Kugui to be the editor of the Yokai Encyclopedia's second volume. As for Alk and co., they are meant to watch over Kugui, as her power brought a painting to life and destroyed her village when she was younger—though she doesn't have clear memories of the incident. The group travels to visit Inaho, who demands a battle before she assists them.
4: Inaho brings the group to Gramp Zigza, who is less than pleased to hear that Kugui wants to interfere with the encyclopedia's creation. Just as he is about to kick them out, his disciple Ryouki interrupts and gives Kugui a chance to show off her art. Now intrigued, Gramp Zigza proposes a competition between Ryouki and Kugui—if Kugui wins, she'll be allowed to be the encyclopedia's editor. Ryouki and Kugui accept, and they are given a week to improve their yokai art.
8: Kugui learns that Ryouki has only been painting for 3 months and is briefly crestfallen by how much more talented Ryouki is. However, her resolve not to lose is strengthened. She finishes a yokai painting and, under the encouragement of Light and co., brings it to life, but is ultimately unable to control it. The group prepares to take the creation down.
12: Ryouki tries to cheer up Kugui, who is depressed at how she could not control her creation, with a new idea—paint a fake yokai and see if this one will behave. Ryouki brings Kugui a painting of a dragon she made up, but Kugui somehow recognizes it. Feeling her memories come back, Kugui paints the dragon and brings it to life. Unfortunately, the creation immediately attacks.
14: With Suizen and Mizuchi's help, Alk and co. are able to put down the dragon. Suizen explains that the dragon is actually a shikigami that has bound itself to Kugui, and that it might be the same creature that destroyed her village when she was younger. Disheartened and fearful of hurting more people, Kugui states that she will never paint again and secludes herself in her room. Ryouki, however, refuses to let things stand and decides to find a way to help Kugui.
15: Kugui locks herself in her room, despite Ryouki and co.'s attempts to coax her out. Suizen offers a suggestion—travel to Kugui's home village, in order to ascertain the dragon's true nature and learn more about Kugui. Taking the suggestion, Ryouki bursts into Kugui's room and drags her out on a date, before leading her and the rest of the group to the village.
19: At the ravaged village, Ryouki explains to Kugui that she aspires to paint like her, and that her art has the potential to make dreams come true. She cheekily prods at Kugui's pride, claiming that she'll one day overtake the disheartened girl if she quits painting now. The two have a heart-to-heart, and Kugui resolves to paint again.
23: Kugui realizes the dragon is a manifestation of her fears, and in order to fully control her power, she must conquer the dragon first. With her pride and her life on the line, she summons the dragon once more for a final showdown.
25: Kugui dreams of her past, finally remembering how she first learned of the dragon. When she wakes, it is time for the competition. She and Ryouki finish painting their yokai, but Gramp Zigza insists that Kugui brings them to life for a grand finale—one that involves an epic battle.
27: Suizen and Mizuchi reflect over the past week and Kugui's growth. In the meantime, Alk and co. visit Gramp Zigza, hoping to see Kugui, but she is out with Ryouki in the mountains. The two girls have another heart-to-heart, treasuring the bond they have with one another, as they enjoy another day of art and adventure.

1: Phiria, not knowing how to befriend former enemies Arly and Arum, asks Alk and co. for advice. Stella suggests going shopping together, and so the group heads into Palpebra while celebrations for the Kaleidoscope's 50th anniversary are underway.
2: Palpebra and the Farlands officially establish a partnership treaty. Meanwhile, Phiria tries her best to befriend Arly, but their shopping trip is interrupted by a surprise dragon attack.
4: Azrail is attacked by assassins, but his fellow Farlan countrymen Yuwel and Celtie come to the rescue. Celtie's brother Ciel reveals that the sacred relic that Palpebra lent to the Farlands was stolen, and assigns Celtie the job of catching the thief. Elsewhere, Arly desperately tries to find Arum, whom she lost track of.
5: Celtie chases down the mysterious thieves, but loses track of their leader. Later, Arum unknowingly runs into the main thief, Orgus, and naively extends him a helping hand, having been taught to aid anyone in need.
6: Arly stops to save a pair of sisters, but ends up being saved herself by Hanabi. She tells Hanabi that Arum is missing, and together they go searching for her. Meanwhile, Alk and co. team up with Celtie to take down a particularly menacing dragon.
9: Alk and Celtie take down the dragon. Meanwhile, Arum saves Orgus from Procheon, the true mastermind behind the dragon attack and theft of the relic. Procheon uses a mysterious bell to take over Arum's mind, forcing her to attack Hanabi and Arly.
10: All parties converge where Arum is being controlled by Procheon, but before the gang can save her, Procheon summons more dragons to cover himself as he escapes with Arum. The group question Orgus on what he knows about Procheon, before Regis shows up claiming to know where Procheon is hiding.
11: Regis explains that he did business with Procheon, but was suspicious of the man and attached a tracker to him. He traces the tracker's signal to the inside of the Kaleidoscope. Celtie and Hanabi stay behind to protect Palpebra, while the rest make their way to confront Procheon.
12: Procheon uses the sacred relic to seal the gang's abilities. He traps them inside a shift, revealing his plans before ringing the same bell to try and take control of Phiria.
13: Arum resists Procheon's control, inspiring the others to break free of Procheon's binds. Driven into a corner by Phiria's powers of light, and robbed of further dragon reinforcements, Procheon takes drastic measures and alters his own body.
15: The dark mage of the Kaleidoscope appears, taking the sacred relic into custody and vanishing after a vague warning. The group returns to the surface victorious, where various loose ends are tied up. Back in Starview, Arum asks Alk to teach her how to bake cookies as the gang enjoys each other's company.

1: The talented chef Parfait is in charge of the pièce de résistance for this year's Valentine's festival. There's only one problem—she's obsessed with monster ingredients. Pur Lilie hires the Starview crew to make sure Parfait's culinary contribution doesn't get too grotesque.
4: Alk and co. help Parfait harvest her first monster ingredient: cacao fruit, which screams when cracked open. Though Light is completely unnerved, a little taste-testing is all it takes to win Alk's seal of approval.
7: Parfait proves herself willing to compromise when she abandons her plan to roast the whole rear end of a bee-like monster, and instead only extracts its syrup. Alk and Stella grow more and more invested in Monster Cuisine, arousing the consternation of Light and Nimbus.
9: After Alk and co. help Parfait milk a chimera, they learn the chef needs one last grisly ingredient: dragon's blood. Light shudders, thinking of vampires and other creatures of the night, but the rest easily discount his concerns.
12: Alk helps Parfait finish her Valentine's creation: a giant chocolate phoenix. However, due to a mix-up in deliveries, the blood candy meant for the eyes was swapped out for golem cores, and the giant cocoa bird comes alive to terrorize Palpebra.
14: Parfait and her companions quickly bring the ravaging food art under control, and Lilie manages to write the battle off as an elaborate opening ceremony. After that, the Valentine's festival goes off without a hitch. Parfait, always eager to discover new ingredients, decides to join Alk and co. on their journey.

1: Deep within old ruins, Rashid awakens Sotieth, a weapon of the ancients. Elsewhere, Alk and co. search through the desert to find ancient ruins before the kingdom beats them to it.
2: Alk and friends are dragged into the Golden Dawn's plan to free enslaved people. Right when they are about to escape, a man named Haridal stands in their way.
6: On the way to the Golden Dawn's hideout, Rashid explains to everyone about his history with Haridal, his former best friend.
10: While the rest of the hideout enjoys a rowdy party, Rashid worries over the Golden Dawn's future. Meanwhile, Haridal leads an army toward their hideout.
11: Unable to reconcile their different visions for a new borderlands, Haridal and Rashid clash, but are interrupted by a timely arrival from Nimbus and co.
13: Pushed into a corner by Haridal's attack, members of the Golden Dawn take Rashid hostage and force Sotieth to activate the Titan.
15: Haridal despairs at the Titan's overwhelming might, but Nimbus snaps him out of it. The two of them go to rescue Rashid and the others from an attack.
19: After receiving first aid, Rashid joins up with the others. Just when the Titan is about to obliterate them, Nephtim shows up just in time to help.
20: With Denah, Nephtim, and Alk's help, Rashid and co. manage to get inside the Titan. However, the guardians within begin to attack.
24: In an effort to free Sotieth, Alk and co. prepare to face the Titan's core.
26: Once the dust settles, Sotieth joins Alk and co. in Starview. Rashid and Haridal share a quiet heart to heart, during which Haridal swears to carry on his friend's work to usher in a new dawn for the borderlands.

2: Alk receives a request from King Johnson to teach Nate about being a hero.
4: After messing up a job by leaving Alk behind, Nate and Alk rethink their strategy. Seeing this, King Johnson gives Alk his own motorcycle so he can keep up.
6: After a cryptic talk with King Johnson, Nate and Alk head out for a job, only to run into a Noxel Group hero, Themis.

10: Nate awakes in a cage, where she angrily questions Themis' motives. After Alk and Regis come to her rescue, she states she doesn't want to lose to someone who gave up on being a hero.

15: Alk and Nate head into battle with the Unification AI, which has moved to a smaller machine to escape being dismantled. Nate and Alk join forces with Themis and other fighters from Starview in the final showdown with the raging AI.
17: In front of the fallen Unification AI, Themis and Nate finally give each other their reasons for being a hero. Days later, Alk and Nate are out shopping when they run into Themis again. 1: After some prodding from Inaho, the gang heads to Paradise Isle for a vacation. Among them is Shywe, determined to make her prophesized marriage to Alk a reality.
2: When Shywe tries to show the wonders of the sprites to Alk, she suddenly loses her connection to the sprites and strands them on a mysterious island. Still recovering from the fall, she and Alk are soon surrounded by hungry animals.
3: As Shywe acclimates to life without the power of the sprites, Alk does his best to provide them with food and shelter. That night, Shywe senses a mysterious power.
4: Back on Paradise Isle, Nimbus and the rest of the gang split up to find their missing friends. Meanwhile, Alk and Shywe stumble upon an amnesiac Sohvi.
5: When an abnormally normal Sohvi guides Alk and Shywe to the building she awoke in, they are accosted by a ferocious creature crying out for his love.
7: Just as Nimbus and co. find Alk and Shywe's footprints, Light contacts them with information on the island and its relation to the Devourer of Stars. Meanwhile, Alk, Shywe, and Sohvi arrive at a mysterious research facility.
8: Just as the failed experiments corner Alk, Sohvi, and Shywe, Nimbus and the gang come to their rescue.
9: Sohvi, having regained her memories, guides the gang to Deophrastus. Just as the group comes face-to-face with the mad scientist, Deo proclaims he will surpass humanity before being enveloped in a bright light.
10: Despite acquiring the power of the Devourer of Stars, Deophrastus continues to draw out more power, causing the world to begin falling apart. Just then, Shywe receives a prophecy that, in order to reclaim her powers, she must sacrifice Alk.
11: By refusing the false prophecy of the Devourer of Stars, Shywe finally learns to prioritize her own will. A powerful sprite reacts to her newfound passion and appears before her. With this new ally, Shywe and Alk take on Deophrastus.
13: Upon returning to Paradise Isle, Shywe is confronted with the reality of her feelings for Alk. Confused by this new emotion, Shywe tries to flee, but her friends pull her back before she can get herself into trouble again.

1: In the middle of a thunderstorm, Magnos catches up to Teo. However, Helga saves Teo at the last moment and escapes with him.
2: Teo saves a parent and child from dogfolk soldiers, but paints himself as a monster in the process. Though Teo regrets stepping in, Helga comforts him and helps him be confident in doing the right thing.
4: After Helga and Teo have a heart-to-heart, Shuilong arrives to ruin the moment.
5: Magnos reveals his plan to change the world and asks Teo to join him, but Teo refuses. When Alk and Nimbus come to the rescue, Magnos uses the Royal Key, the sacred relic Teo had in his possession, to make his dogfolk soldiers run rampant.
7: Teo learns about himself through a conversation with Helga. He resolves to join Alk and the others in their mission to put a stop to Magnos' plan.
9: While Helga keeps Shuilong at bay, Teo and the others find Magnos. With the Crown of the Beast King in arm's reach, Magnos reveals his innermost thoughts.
10: Though Teo pleads with Magnos, the lionfolk man activates the Royal Key and transforms. Teo resolves to save him with Alk and Nimbus' help.
12: Magnos throws Teo to the side and is crushed by rubble in his place. Teo, though distraught at failing to save Magnos, resolves to help other people like Magnos. Joined by Claw, Albert, and Helga, he looks to the future with hope.

1: Rooma sees his first and last memory after Capella ejects him from the research lab.
2: Couette and Rooma end up in trouble inside a dream. Couette calls upon Stella, who joins the dream and uses the power of imagination to fight back. They hop aboard a ship and sail off.
4: In order to fix Rooma, Couette asks Marina and friends to help her search for Curse Crystals.
6: After defeating the dragon, the group gathers enough Curse Crystals to restore function to Rooma. Rooma asks for help as the group realizes that a Star Augur is involved.
7: After bringing Rooma to Capella, the robot begins to absorb the life force around him and displays the Mark of a Dragon.
8: Capella explains Rooma's true form and asks the group to kill him. Marina, hearing this, kidnaps Rooma and Couette. They make their getaway aboard their battleship, but Vagner soon chases after them.
9: With a little push from Nimbus and Marina, Couette decides to face the others and ask them to help her save Rooma. Capella shows up and reveals her true aim: to revive the dragon of darkness, Armadeus.
10: Negotiations break down as Couette refuses to let Capella get rid of Rooma to revive Armadeus. Capella summons a fake Champion that absorbs Rooma. In response, Couette asks her friends to help rescue him.
12: Rooma decides to be reborn as Armadeus, but promises Couette that he won't forget her. Couette, believing in that promise, resolves to move forward and pursue more knowledge.

1: Alk and friends travel to an unexplored forest for a job, where they discover a castle and its town in the distance. As they approach, they see a mysterious robed man and the prince Razelt under attack, and drop in to save them.
4: The robed man introduces himself as Simon, and reveals that the town and castle were made by the princess Prika through creation magic. He asks the group to check on Prika in the castle, which they agree to. As they travel through town, Razelt accidentally discovers how fragile the structures are, before more Poppets appear and attack.
7: Alk and friends arrive at the castle, where they are verbally assaulted by Prika who mistakes them for someone else. The princess quickly realizes her mistake and invites them inside, eager to host people for the first time ever. She explains that her retainer Grey is missing, and that her only contact with the outside world is through letters with Prince Frau of Mosnia.
10: After comparing information, Prika reveals she has no idea why her Poppets are out of control, nor who Simon is. Her confusion only grows when Razelt tells her Mosnia was destroyed over 300 years ago. Determined to get answers, Prika grabs her prince's letters and asks Alk and friends to bring her to Simon.
13: While Alk and Razelt try to get the town gate open, Prika nervously explains that she has never gone outside before, but Stella is quick to calm her down. Simon suddenly appears from behind them, revealing that Prika is a weapon, and Grey was supposed to be her warden, before he attacks the group.
15: With the group in a pinch, Prika blasts open the gate and leads the group in a retreat, stepping into the outside world for the first time. That night, she has a heart-to-heart with Stella, who helps her acknowledge that her good memories with the prince were real, even if the prince himself wasn't.
18: Prika and company find the ruins of Mosnia, and confirm that Razelt spoke true—Mosnia hasn't existed for hundreds of years. Though her prince was never real, Prika is content enough to know that he was her friend, and that now she has Alk and company to call friends too. Determined to learn the truth about Grey, Prika asks everyone to take her back to Simon.
21: Alk and friends discover a letter and a will inside Simon's cabin, which reveal that Grey has passed away, and Prika is no princess. Simon reappears, blaming Prika's bloodline for the destruction of Mosnia, and claims that he will end her to free them from the curse of her existence.
24: In the middle of Simon's assault, Prika runs out to talk with him and follows him for a private conversation. Tensions come to a head, and the two face off with Poppets. Simon is finally driven into a corner, and summons up a decade's worth of mana to create Cair Oblivion.
26: Prika defeats Simon with one huge blow that reduces most of the town to rubble. In the aftermath, Prika pours her heart out to Simon and asks him to bring them to Grey's grave. There, the two have an earnest conversation and make up, with Prika deciding that they will be siblings from now on. Free from her castle confines at last, Prika parts with everyone, ready to see the world.

20: The group find themselves in a tight situation surrounded by Noxel enforcers when a man in an armored vehicle comes to their rescue. He introduces himself as King Johnson, the CEO of PBC, an AltMeme subsidiary. With no other viable methods of escape available, the group accepts his help.
24: The group finds Bulleta sulking in a tavern alone, reflecting on her recent fallout with Love. After Alk and company help her reaffirm her feelings, Bulleta finds the motivation to patch things up with Love.
28: While the Noxel and AltMeme enforcers engage in battle, the Conductor confirms Love's orders once again before facing off against Bulleta and the others in a final showdown.
30: After taking down the Conductor once again, Bulleta makes her way to Mother Love. Leaving nothing off the table, the estranged partners have a final clash of ideals and weapons.
32: The final attack between Bulleta and Love breaks a hole in the dome above, revealing a portion of the real sky. Love eventually steps down from her position at DAN and joins Bulleta to finally explore the skies together.
1: On the rooftops of Qualia City, a city that has been in business for 520 years, a mercenary named Bulleta and her partner Love spot a ray of light in the distance. Sensing a call to adventure, they make their way toward it.
2: Bulleta saves Alk and the others from an attacker known as the Conductor. Love advises them to become troubleshooters if they hope to make a living in Qualia City, a place governed entirety by corporate ethos.
6: While enjoying their meal of AdTaste-flavored SoyMate, Alk and the others learn of AltMeme and Noxel, the two corporations that dominate Qualia City. Using their newly found intel, the group discovers that their attacker was working for DayAndNight, a Noxel Group subsidiary.
10: Bulleta decides to help Alk and the others infiltrate DAN, in hopes of showing her best friend what the real sky looks like beyond the neon skyline.
14: As Alk and the others head deeper into the DAN facility, the Conductor appears before them and takes a new weapon formation, codename: Big Band.
16: The Conductor, having been defeated, allows the group to pass. As they approach the altar, they're blindsided by an attack from Love, who reveals herself to be Mother Love, the true president of DAN. Bulleta uses a smoke bomb to narrowly escape with the others.

1: In the middle of a thunderstorm, Magnos catches up to Teo. However, Helga saves Teo at the last moment and escapes with him.
2: Teo saves a parent and child from dogfolk soldiers, but paints himself as a monster in the process. Though Teo regrets stepping in, Helga comforts him and helps him be confident in doing the right thing.
4: After Helga and Teo have a heart-to-heart, Shuilong arrives to ruin the moment.
5: Magnos reveals his plan to change the world and asks Teo to join him, but Teo refuses. When Alk and Nimbus come to the rescue, Magnos uses the Royal Key, the sacred relic Teo had in his possession, to make his dogfolk soldiers run rampant.
7: Teo learns about himself through a conversation with Helga. He resolves to join Alk and the others in their mission to put a stop to Magnos' plan.
9: While Helga keeps Shuilong at bay, Teo and the others find Magnos. With the Crown of the Beast King in arm's reach, Magnos reveals his innermost thoughts.
10: Though Teo pleads with Magnos, the lionfolk man activates the Royal Key and transforms. Teo resolves to save him with Alk and Nimbus' help.
12: Magnos throws Teo to the side and is crushed by rubble in his place. Teo, though distraught at failing to save Magnos, resolves to help other people like Magnos. Joined by Claw, Albert, and Helga, he looks to the future with hope.

1: With the battle at the Palace of Stars behind them, spring has come for Alk and his friends at last. A joint graduation ceremony is in the works to honor the students of Shibuya and Voluntas Academy, and although Alk struggles with the loss of his eye, he pitches in to ensure that the event will be a success.
2: Alk and co. find themselves on different paths as Marina disbands the Crimson Blades, Nimbus joins the Abyss Exploration Team, and Light reveals his plans to join Lilith as her advisor. Hearing that her friends are leaving, Nephtim is distraught. To ease her loneliness, Stella resumes work on her book to commemorate the group's adventures together.
3: Alk and his friends go back to where their journey first began in the Garden of the Sprites to interview their forest friends about their future plans. Alk declines Lilith's invitation to become a politician, and the group discusses future plans for a student exchange program between Shibuya and the other worlds.
4: As preparations for the joint graduation ceremony are underway, the members of Voluntas Academy envision new plans for the future while the Guild Knights, the Vesta, and the adventurers plan to stay their course. And although Alk has come of age, he confides in Yuwel that he is still unsure of his path ahead.
5: With preparations for the school's grand reopening and joint graduation ceremony complete, Alk and the gang have a party to let loose. Under the ever-watchful gaze of Nimbus, Alk has his first pint. While their friends reminisce about the past, Alk considers his own plans for the future after some prodding from Selgir.
6: The school's grand reopening begins, bringing a jam-packed day of excitement and filling the people of Palpebra with hope for the future. But right on cue, Tharros goes haywire and the group is forced into battle. Unable to resist the nostalgia of fighting golems with his friends, Alk joins the fray once more.
8: Just after Alk receives his diploma, Nao returns just in time to deliver a moving graduation speech. After the ceremony, everyone gathers to share their dreams for what lies ahead, and Stella informs the group that she is almost ready to unveil her new book.
9: With the cherry blossoms in bloom, Alk and co. take their first steps into the future. Alk joins the Abyss Exploration Team while training as a chef at Parfait's restaurant. Stella continues her duties as Keeper of Starview Village, promising to keep chronicling everyone's adventures—because for the Champions of the Stars, the journey has only just begun.

1: News that monsters have once again become active in the Farlands stirs up Yuwel's memories of the catastrophe of five years ago. However, accompanied by Libram and the others, he resolves to go back to his country to protect its people.
2: While fending off monsters with Nimbus and the others, Yuwel meets Varen, the crown prince. He then visits House Swes and agrees to join Varen in speaking with House Tris about dealing with the impending catastrophe.
3: Varen's attempt to persuade Ciel, the lord of House Tris, fails as there is another person he needs to speak with first. Marden, the second-born son of House Oxtan, appears and reveals that he knows of the Star Augurs and their involvement with the peace treaty ceremony. Varen decides to team up with Marden.
4: Marden reveals a research facility allegedly used by the Star Augurs, where they can obtain blackmail for use against the Oxtans. Varen is initially opposed to the idea, but a conversation with Yuwel convinces him to see where this path takes him.
5: Yuwel and Varen arrive in the Oxtans' territory and speak with one of their nobles. A fortuitous explosion reveals the research facility they're searching for, with clear signs of the Star Augurs' involvement. Marden attempts to force information out of the Oxtan noble, even speaking of the princess's assassination from years ago.
6: Varen cuts off Marden's threats and offers to save the Oxtan noble instead. Returning to House Swes, Varen and allies discuss next steps to secure more allied Houses. To that end, Yuwel decides to reform the Swallow Knights.
7: Receiving support from many capable allies, the Swallow Knights are reformed with Yuwel as their captain. Aided by both House Nouin and House Tris, the knights and Varen get ready to face the monster threat.
8: The Swallow Knights combine forces with Houses Nouin and Tris to quell the rampaging monsters. Back in the research facility, Varen and friends confront Marden, who summons a terrifying creature out of desperation.
10: Varen's unbending faith in the light brings Marden back from the brink. With the monsters quelled, things settle down as Yuwel returns to Palpebra. While speaking with his old comrade Will, Yuwel runs into Varen, who has come over to study abroad. The two look forward to spending even more time with each other.

1: Rooma sees his first and last memory after Capella ejects him from the research lab.
2: Couette and Rooma end up in trouble inside a dream. Couette calls upon Stella, who joins the dream and uses the power of imagination to fight back. They hop aboard a ship and sail off.
4: In order to fix Rooma, Couette asks Marina and friends to help her search for Curse Crystals.
6: After defeating the dragon, the group gathers enough Curse Crystals to restore function to Rooma. Rooma asks for help as the group realizes that a Star Augur is involved.
7: After bringing Rooma to Capella, the robot begins to absorb the life force around him and displays the Mark of a Dragon.
8: Capella explains Rooma's true form and asks the group to kill him. Marina, hearing this, kidnaps Rooma and Couette. They make their getaway aboard their battleship, but Vagner soon chases after them.
9: With a little push from Nimbus and Marina, Couette decides to face the others and ask them to help her save Rooma. Capella shows up and reveals her true aim: to revive the dragon of darkness, Armadeus.
10: Negotiations break down as Couette refuses to let Capella get rid of Rooma to revive Armadeus. Capella summons a fake Champion that absorbs Rooma. In response, Couette asks her friends to help rescue him.
12: Rooma decides to be reborn as Armadeus, but promises Couette that he won't forget her. Couette, believing in that promise, resolves to move forward and pursue more knowledge.

9: Alk and Celtie take down the dragon. Meanwhile, Arum saves Orgus from Procheon, the true mastermind behind the dragon attack and theft of the relic. Procheon uses a mysterious bell to take over Arum's mind, forcing her to attack Hanabi and Arly.
10: All parties converge where Arum is being controlled by Procheon, but before the gang can save her, Procheon summons more dragons to cover himself as he escapes with Arum. The group question Orgus on what he knows about Procheon, before Regis shows up claiming to know where Procheon is hiding.
11: Regis explains that he did business with Procheon, but was suspicious of the man and attached a tracker to him. He traces the tracker's signal to the inside of the Kaleidoscope. Celtie and Hanabi stay behind to protect Palpebra, while the rest make their way to confront Procheon.
12: Procheon uses the sacred relic to seal the gang's abilities. He traps them inside a shift, revealing his plans before ringing the same bell to try and take control of Phiria.
13: Arum resists Procheon's control, inspiring the others to break free of Procheon's binds. Driven into a corner by Phiria's powers of light, and robbed of further dragon reinforcements, Procheon takes drastic measures and alters his own body.
15: The dark mage of the Kaleidoscope appears, taking the sacred relic into custody and vanishing after a vague warning. The group returns to the surface victorious, where various loose ends are tied up. Back in Starview, Arum asks Alk to teach her how to bake cookies as the gang enjoys each other's company.
1: Phiria, not knowing how to befriend former enemies Arly and Arum, asks Alk and co. for advice. Stella suggests going shopping together, and so the group heads into Palpebra while celebrations for the Kaleidoscope's 50th anniversary are underway.
2: Palpebra and the Farlands officially establish a partnership treaty. Meanwhile, Phiria tries her best to befriend Arly, but their shopping trip is interrupted by a surprise dragon attack.
4: Azrail is attacked by assassins, but his fellow Farlan countrymen Yuwel and Celtie come to the rescue. Celtie's brother Ciel reveals that the sacred relic that Palpebra lent to the Farlands was stolen, and assigns Celtie the job of catching the thief. Elsewhere, Arly desperately tries to find Arum, whom she lost track of.
5: Celtie chases down the mysterious thieves, but loses track of their leader. Later, Arum unknowingly runs into the main thief, Orgus, and naively extends him a helping hand, having been taught to aid anyone in need.
6: Arly stops to save a pair of sisters, but ends up being saved herself by Hanabi. She tells Hanabi that Arum is missing, and together they go searching for her. Meanwhile, Alk and co. team up with Celtie to take down a particularly menacing dragon.

1: Instead of their typical annual school event, Voluntas Academy holds Magia Fest with the people of Shibuya this year. Nao excitedly explains the festival Dia. Elsewhere, Alk, Mr. Takamori, and other people of importance meet with Luciada, the academy's student council president, in order to prepare for the event.
2: Despite many trials and tribulations, the last day of Magia Fest arrives. The last main event is the concert, but unfortunately, the scheduled singer has a last minute accident. A chance encounter leaves Dia in charge of the performance. Afterward, Luciada has a chance run in with Liam, whom she recognizes much to everyone else's surprise.
3: Revealing that Liam used to be her private tutor, Luciada ropes him into helping their group solve trouble around the festival. They eventually come to the conclusion that the staggering number of issues must be caused, at least in part, by cultural differences between the Palpebrans and Shibuyans. After two students bad-mouth Luciada, another student comes running for help regarding rampaging golems.
5: A child is nearly crushed by falling debris, but a student from Shibuya saves him in time. The student reluctantly introduces herself as Hibiki Suminami, a person who was discovered in the Kaleidoscope and rescued from the Abyss. She grows irritated and eventually explodes at Luciada's overly optimistic goals about Shibuya and Palpebra working together, before growing embarrassed and running away. She runs into Toria immediately after.
6: Toria drags Hibiki around the festival, eventually prying out of the girl that she feels alienated from the other Shibuyans, as she wasn't there when her home vanished from Japan. Just as Hibiki starts speaking about her hobby of writing music, she realizes her notebook is gone. Toria takes her to the student council room for the lost and found, where Hibiki discovers, to her shock, that her song Binary Planet is the one being performed for the festival's concert.
7: Greatly upset that even her own song has seemingly left her behind, Hibiki teleports away, accidentally ending up next to a sample of a serpent and resonating with it. A cloaked man appears, trapping her in magic and forcing her to resonate again, when Luciada and the others come to the rescue. They manage to free Hibiki, but almost all the other Shibuyans at the festival begin to resonate with the sample.
8: Spurred on by dark magic, the Shibuyans drown in their hidden worries and start fading away from reality. Luciada rushes to her sound relay system and offers words of reassurance, slowly dragging everyone out of their dark mood. To help reassure the Shibuyans they aren't alone, Dia convinces Hibiki to perform Binary Planet with her, while Alk and the others fend off the revived serpent running amok.
10: Returned to their senses, the awakened people of Shibuya wish from their hearts to protect the Binary Planet performance, culminating in reality changing briefly so that the big mecha golem is capable of firing a laser at the serpent. With the battle won and day saved, Luciada and Hibiki make amends, and another performance of Binary Planet is held to celebrate.
